items.title: Musk urges Bezos to throw an ‘epic wedding’ after Amazon founder blasts report of $600 million nuptials as ‘completely false’
items.description: Bezos flatly denied a report he would marry fiancée Lauren Sánchez the weekend after Christmas in a lavish ceremony in Aspen.

items.title: Surging cases and lagging vaccines: Why this U.S. flu season has experts worried
items.description: Thirteen states reported high or very high levels of flu-like illness last week, about double from the week before.

items.title: The alleged online smear campaign against Blake Lively is a reminder of how eager society is to ‘hate on women’
items.description: The "It Ends With Us" actress was likely the victim of an online smear campaign.

items.title: Trump’s demand for control of Greenland is immediately rejected
items.description: Greenland’s PM: “Greenland is ours. We are not for sale and will never be for sale.”

items.title: Half of companies with office space say leases are affecting their RTO policies
items.description: Companies say they want to increase worker collaboration productivity, but many leaders are also influenced by existing office leases.
